==Icelandic==
===Pronunciation===
{{IPA|[ˈd̥øyːðʏr]}}
===Etymology===
Old Norse ''[[dauðr]]''
===Adjective===
'''dauður'''

# [[dead]]

====Synonyms====
[[dáinn]] (past participle of [[deyja]] (to [[die]]))

====Usage note====
'''dauður''' can sound heartless in modern Icelandic when used for someone the speaker, or the people he is speaking to, knew. When referring to a specific person, use [[dáinn]] instead, unless you are talking about a historical figure long gone or someone you didn't care about.

